  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed operating points and a comprehensive UQ campaign documented sensitivity of the hemolysis index to inlet boundary conditions, fluid viscosity, and turbulence model coefficients. All 13 credibility factors were assessed; seven achieved levels below required levels and six were flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Decision: Not accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-vad-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-vad-hemolysis-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-piv-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-hemolysis-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-mc-uq-samples-5000runs"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-piv-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison — FDA generic centrifugal pump",
      "description": "Computational velocity fields compared against particle image velocimetry measurements at five operating points. The UQ campaign (5000 Monte Carlo draws) quantified sensitivity of predicted hemolysis index to inlet turbulence intensity, viscosity uncertainty, and mesh resolution; sensitivity rankings were documented in the UQ campaign report. Mean absolute error in axial velocity below 8% at all stations; however, hemolysis index predictions exceeded experimental measurements by 35–60% at high-speed low-flow conditions, driving the Not Accepted outcome."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index absolute-level validation — five operating points",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis compared against in-vitro measurements at 2500, 3000, 3500, 4000, and 4500 RPM at design flow. Monte Carlo uncertainty bands were computed; sensitivity analysis within the UQ campaign identified turbulence model form as the dominant uncertainty contributor, yet the structured credibility link for sensitivity analysis was not formally registered in the package metadata. Validation ratio outside acceptance band at three of five operating points."
    }
  ],
